sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Validating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS 1.2+ mTLS
    participant Operator as KubeRay Operator<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    participant HeadPod as Ray Head Pod<br/>GCS + Dashboard
    participant Workers as Ray Worker Pods
    participant Autoscaler as Autoscaler Sidecar
    participant ServeSvc as Ray Serve Service<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS 1.2+

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1: RayCluster Creation and Management

    User->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster CR<br/>kubectl apply -f raycluster.yaml<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-ray-io-v1-raycluster<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation Result
    K8sAPI-->>User: RayCluster Created

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch RayCluster CR<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: RayCluster Event

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Head Pod<br/>HTTPS/6443
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Head Services<br/>HTTPS/6443
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS/6443

    Workers->>HeadPod: Connect to GCS<br/>6379/TCP TCP<br/>Optional TLS<br/>Optional Password

    Note over User,S3: Flow 2: Ray Job Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: Create RayJob CR<br/>kubectl apply -f rayjob.yaml<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Job Submitter Pod<br/>HTTPS/6443
    Operator->>HeadPod: Submit Job via Ray Client<br/>10001/TCP TCP<br/>Optional TLS + mTLS

    HeadPod->>Workers: Distribute Tasks<br/>6379/TCP TCP<br/>Optional TLS
    HeadPod->>S3: Load Data/Models<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>AWS IAM/Keys
    S3-->>HeadPod: Model Artifacts
    Workers->>S3: Load Data<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    S3-->>Workers: Data Chunks
    Workers-->>HeadPod: Task Results
    HeadPod-->>User: Job Status via Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,S3: Flow 3: Ray Serve Inference

    User->>ServeSvc: POST /predict<br/>8000/TCP HTTP<br/>Optional TLS<br/>Optional Bearer Token
    ServeSvc->>HeadPod: Coordination Request<br/>6379/TCP TCP<br/>Optional TLS
    HeadPod->>Workers: Execute Inference<br/>Internal Ray Protocol
    Workers->>S3: Load Model (if needed)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    S3-->>Workers: Model Artifacts
    Workers-->>HeadPod: Inference Result
    HeadPod-->>ServeSvc: Response
    ServeSvc-->>User: JSON Response

    Note over User,S3: Flow 4: Autoscaling

    Autoscaler->>HeadPod: Query Cluster State<br/>8265/TCP HTTP<br/>No Auth
    HeadPod-->>Autoscaler: Pending Tasks
    Autoscaler->>K8sAPI: Scale Worker Pods<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Worker Pod Events
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Delete Workers<br/>HTTPS/6443

    Note over User,S3: Flow 5: Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>Operator: Scrape Metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    Operator-->>Prometheus: Operator Metrics
    Prometheus->>HeadPod: Scrape Metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    HeadPod-->>Prometheus: Ray Cluster Metrics
    Prometheus->>Workers: Scrape Metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    Workers-->>Prometheus: Worker Metrics
